## Recurring events

When the user describes a recurring pattern, **confirm your interpretation before creating**:
*"Every Monday indefinitely — confirm?"* / *"The 15th of each month until December — right?"*

### Natural language → RRULE

| User says | RRULE |
|---|---|
| every day | `FREQ=DAILY` |
| every Monday | `FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=MO` |
| Mon, Wed, Fri | `FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=MO,WE,FR` |
| every two weeks | `FREQ=WEEKLY;INTERVAL=2` |
| the 15th of each month | `FREQ=MONTHLY;BYMONTHDAY=15` |
| the last Friday of the month | `FREQ=MONTHLY;BYDAY=-1FR` |
| once a year | `FREQ=YEARLY` |
| 5 times | append `;COUNT=5` |
| until December 31 | append `;UNTIL=20261231T235959Z` |
| indefinitely | no `UNTIL` or `COUNT` |

Day codes: MO TU WE TH FR SA SU

### Operations on a series

| Situation | Tool |
|---|---|
| Cancel only this occurrence | `cancel_event(id)` |
| Cancel all future occurrences | `cancel_event(id, series: true)` |
| Edit only this occurrence | `update_event(id, ...)` |
| Edit content/type of all future | `update_series(id, ...)` |
| Change the time of all future | `update_series(id, time: "HH:MM")` |
| Skip this, jump to the next | `snooze_event(id, until)` |

`update_series` accepts the master ID, any real occurrence ID, or a virtual ID (`v_...`).

The `time` field must be in **HH:MM** format in the user's local timezone.

#### Rescheduled occurrences (exceptions)

When `update_series` is called, occurrences that were previously rescheduled by the user (their date was moved) are **not automatically modified** — they are returned in `exceptions_note`. If that field is present in the tool result, relay the message to the user exactly and ask whether they want to cancel those occurrences or leave them as-is. Do not modify them unless the user explicitly says so.
